results.name: Irregular triangle read by rows with trailing zeros removed where T(n,k) is the number of unlabeled simple graphs with n vertices whose edge-set has non-spanning edge-connectivity k.
comment: The non-spanning edge-connectivity of a graph is the minimum number of edges that must be removed to obtain a disconnected or empty graph, ignoring isolated vertices.
link: Gus Wiseman, Unlabeled graphs with 5 vertices, organized by non-spanning edge-connectivity (isolated vertices not shown).
results.author: _Gus Wiseman_, Sep 03 2019
